WEBVTT

1
00:02:44.960 --> 00:02:49.816
Financial times. 100 index of 11
points just above the key 3.800 level.

2
00:02:49.840 --> 00:02:54.800
As for the rest of Europe. Frankfurt's
DAX gaining 9 points to 25.32.

3
00:02:54.970 --> 00:02:58.800
In Paris. the CAC-40 losing 7. the
weaker franc weighing on the market.

4
00:03:13.650 --> 00:03:14.940
Thank you. Ilsa.

5
00:03:16.490 --> 00:03:17.990
Have a nice day.

6
00:03:30.380 --> 00:03:33.590
Actually are on time this morning
according to dispatchers.

7
00:03:33.960 --> 00:03:36.550
San Francisco's freeways are...

8
00:03:51.730 --> 00:03:52.980
Good morning. Sir.

9
00:03:53.400 --> 00:03:55.046
Well. tell me what
we're supposed to do.

10
00:03:55.070 --> 00:03:57.256
I mean. you may be perched
on majority shares.

11
00:03:57.280 --> 00:04:00.110
but we all get fucked
if the actuals crash.

12
00:04:00.530 --> 00:04:01.950
That old man is
going to sink us.

13
00:04:02.080 --> 00:04:05.226
Soon as I have Baer-Grant's
P and I report in hand

14
00:04:05.250 --> 00:04:07.000
I will be speed-dialing
your number.

15
00:04:07.660 --> 00:04:11.016
Is that a promise? I'm sorry.
I'm not aware of that term.

16
00:04:11.040 --> 00:04:14.936
Well. what do I do if Anson calls
about substantiation procedure?

17
00:04:14.960 --> 00:04:17.816
Take evasive action. Have your
secretary say you're in a meeting.

18
00:04:17.840 --> 00:04:19.510
Thank you. Jack.

19
00:04:19.680 --> 00:04:21.196
Yes. Maria. Invitations.

20
00:04:21.220 --> 00:04:23.026
Mmm-hmm. The museum gala.

21
00:04:23.050 --> 00:04:26.196
No. The Fitzwilliam botanical
annual fundraiser.

22
00:04:26.220 --> 00:04:28.576
No. The Hinchberger wedding.

23
00:04:28.600 --> 00:04:30.060
Hinchberger wedding.

24
00:04:31.100 --> 00:04:34.876
Tuxedos. droning conversations.
I don't think so. No.

25
00:04:34.900 --> 00:04:36.280
I'll send your regrets.

26
00:04:36.740 --> 00:04:38.546
Honestly. why must I bother?

27
00:04:38.570 --> 00:04:40.386
You don't know about
society. Maria.

28
00:04:40.410 --> 00:04:43.346
You don't have the
satisfaction of avoiding it.

29
00:04:43.370 --> 00:04:44.886
Yes.

30
00:04:44.910 --> 00:04:47.250
I have an Elizabeth on line 3.

31
00:04:49.120 --> 00:04:50.370
Your ex-wife.

32
00:04:50.580 --> 00:04:51.960
I know who it is.

33
00:04:53.090 --> 00:04:54.630
Take a message.

34
00:04:55.250 --> 00:04:57.210
Oh. Happy Birthday. sir.

35
00:04:58.590 --> 00:04:59.840
Thank you. Maggie.

36
00:05:03.010 --> 00:05:04.616
I don't like her.

37
00:05:04.640 --> 00:05:07.930
I wouldn't even mention the
following. but he was very insistent.

38
00:05:08.100 --> 00:05:10.366
It's obviously some sort of prank.
What?

39
00:05:10.390 --> 00:05:12.586
Well. a gentleman called
requesting to have lunch with you.

40
00:05:12.610 --> 00:05:15.706
I tried to assure him that you
were very busy... What's his name?

41
00:05:15.730 --> 00:05:17.610
A Mr. Seymour Butts.

42
00:05:19.700 --> 00:05:22.530
Under the Bleachers
by Seymour Butts.

43
00:05:23.200 --> 00:05:24.620
I'm sorry?

44
00:05:25.620 --> 00:05:29.636
Cancel my lunch. Make a reservation at
the City Club for myself and Mr. Butts.

45
00:05:29.660 --> 00:05:31.170
My usual table.

46
00:05:33.330 --> 00:05:35.920
Maria. put the reservation
under my name.

47
00:05:41.590 --> 00:05:44.300
You ready to order. sir?
No. I'm still waiting.

48
00:05:44.510 --> 00:05:46.100
This was ice tea.

49
00:05:52.400 --> 00:05:54.560
Conrad. what a surprise.

50
00:05:54.730 --> 00:05:56.230
Happy Birthday. Nickie.

51
00:05:56.480 --> 00:05:57.940
Seymour Butts.

52
00:05:58.280 --> 00:06:00.190
I'll never get
tired of that one.

53
00:06:00.400 --> 00:06:03.336
That's why it's a classic.
This is a nice restaurant.

54
00:06:03.360 --> 00:06:04.466
They gave me a free jacket.

55
00:06:04.490 --> 00:06:06.426
I'm sure they're
gonna want it back.

56
00:06:06.450 --> 00:06:08.216
I remember being here
a long time ago.

57
00:06:08.240 --> 00:06:09.386
Yeah. I took you here once.

58
00:06:09.410 --> 00:06:12.016
No. I used to buy crystal
meth off the maitre d'.

59
00:06:12.040 --> 00:06:13.146
Oh. really?

60
00:06:13.170 --> 00:06:14.266
In college.

61
00:06:14.290 --> 00:06:15.340
Which college?

62
00:06:16.170 --> 00:06:17.130
Touche.

63
00:06:18.210 --> 00:06:19.510
Miss me?

64
00:06:19.960 --> 00:06:21.906
As much as that's possible.

65
00:06:21.930 --> 00:06:23.010
You look good.

66
00:06:23.050 --> 00:06:24.066
So do you.

67
00:06:24.090 --> 00:06:25.300
To think I was worried.

68
00:06:26.050 --> 00:06:27.486
Worried about me?

69
00:06:27.510 --> 00:06:30.600
How long has it been since Mom's funeral?
Two. three years?

70
00:06:32.310 --> 00:06:33.376
I thought you quit.

71
00:06:33.400 --> 00:06:35.456
I did. It didn't take.

72
00:06:35.480 --> 00:06:37.190
Well. you can't smoke here.

73
00:06:37.730 --> 00:06:39.006
I'm with you.

74
00:06:39.030 --> 00:06:42.320
It's illegal to smoke in
restaurants in California.

75
00:06:42.490 --> 00:06:44.070
Fuck California.

76
00:06:45.280 --> 00:06:46.530
How are you?

77
00:06:46.780 --> 00:06:47.990
Couldn't be better.

78
00:06:49.040 --> 00:06:50.176
Elizabeth?

79
00:06:50.200 --> 00:06:53.556
We're divorced. She remarried a
pediatrician or a gynecologist.

80
00:06:53.580 --> 00:06:56.710
or a pediatric gynecologist.
Lives in. uh. Sausalito.

81
00:06:57.290 --> 00:06:58.670
That's too bad.

82
00:06:59.420 --> 00:07:00.630
I liked her.

83
00:07:01.220 --> 00:07:02.720
And what about you?

84
00:07:03.180 --> 00:07:04.866
What. you don't keep
track of me anymore?

85
00:07:04.890 --> 00:07:06.760
Not since family week at rehab.

86
00:07:07.850 --> 00:07:09.890
So what brings you
to town. Conrad?

87
00:07:09.930 --> 00:07:11.180
Everything all right?

88
00:07:11.390 --> 00:07:13.246
Yeah. Need anything?

89
00:07:13.270 --> 00:07:14.730
Nope. Really?

90
00:07:15.150 --> 00:07:17.360
No I don't need anything from you.
I just

91
00:07:17.900 --> 00:07:20.256
found myself laying naked
on the beach near Ibiza.

92
00:07:20.280 --> 00:07:21.900
and all of a sudden it clicked.

93
00:07:22.070 --> 00:07:23.450
October 12th.

94
00:07:23.820 --> 00:07:25.280
Nickie's birthday.

95
00:07:25.450 --> 00:07:26.740
October 11th.

96
00:07:27.320 --> 00:07:28.410
Whatever.

97
00:07:33.210 --> 00:07:34.226
This is for you.

98
00:07:34.250 --> 00:07:35.420
You shouldn't have.

99
00:07:36.580 --> 00:07:39.840
What do you get for the
man who has everything?

100
00:07:44.010 --> 00:07:46.486
"Consumer Recreation Services."

101
00:07:46.510 --> 00:07:48.220
Well. I do have golf clubs.

102
00:07:48.640 --> 00:07:49.760
Call that number.

103
00:07:50.510 --> 00:07:51.560
Why?

104
00:07:51.770 --> 00:07:53.680
It'll make your life fun.

105
00:07:54.730 --> 00:07:55.786
Fun?

106
00:07:55.810 --> 00:07:58.400
You know what that is?
You've seen other people have it.

107
00:07:59.190 --> 00:08:00.916
It's an entertainment service.

108
00:08:00.940 --> 00:08:02.570
An escort service?

109
00:08:03.530 --> 00:08:05.820
A profound life experience.

110
00:08:07.370 --> 00:08:09.096
Sorry. I'll just...

111
00:08:09.120 --> 00:08:10.580
No. that's all right. Just...

112
00:08:12.120 --> 00:08:13.426
Tell me you'll call.

113
00:08:13.450 --> 00:08:15.460
I said I would. No. you didn't.

114
00:08:17.750 --> 00:08:19.290
You still on medication?

115
00:08:20.920 --> 00:08:22.106
Why would you say that?

116
00:08:22.130 --> 00:08:23.696
You gentlemen ready to order?

117
00:08:23.720 --> 00:08:25.236
I didn't mean it the
way it sounded.

118
00:08:25.260 --> 00:08:28.090
I'm not on anything.
I'm not even seeing a shrink.

119
00:08:28.340 --> 00:08:29.866
And I feel great.

120
00:08:29.890 --> 00:08:31.260
Do you mind?

121
00:08:35.140 --> 00:08:37.150
I think you'll like this. I did.

122
00:08:37.350 --> 00:08:39.860
And it was the best thing
that ever happened to me.

123
00:08:40.610 --> 00:08:41.820
I'll call them.

124
00:08:42.030 --> 00:08:43.506
Do it. For you.

125
00:08:43.530 --> 00:08:46.126
I said I'll call. okay?
All right. I'll call.

126
00:08:46.150 --> 00:08:49.160
It's just that. uh.
I hate surprises.

127
00:08:50.030 --> 00:08:51.280
I know.

128
00:08:53.200 --> 00:09:00.380
Happy Birthday to you.

129
00:09:00.500 --> 00:09:04.340
Happy Birthday. Mr. Van Orton.

130
00:09:04.550 --> 00:09:08.300
Happy Birthday to you.

131
00:09:09.930 --> 00:09:10.930
Thank you.

132
00:09:13.810 --> 00:09:17.116
Someone's got to fly to Seattle and
drive a stake through Anson's heart.

133
00:09:17.140 --> 00:09:18.666
Have you seen the
profitability report?

134
00:09:18.690 --> 00:09:21.246
You can imagine how
much more unhappy I am.

135
00:09:21.270 --> 00:09:23.400
So. you're gonna deal with Anson?
That's correct.

136
00:09:23.570 --> 00:09:24.820
We're furious.

137
00:09:25.690 --> 00:09:27.006
Sleep well. Nicholas.

138
00:09:27.030 --> 00:09:28.200
I will.

139
00:10:28.220 --> 00:10:29.340
Good night. Ilsa.

140
00:10:29.760 --> 00:10:30.986
Dinner's in the oven.

141
00:10:31.010 --> 00:10:34.220
Thank you. Oh. I
saw Conrad today.

142
00:10:34.930 --> 00:10:36.470
Did you? How is he?

143
00:10:36.930 --> 00:10:38.060
He's okay.

144
00:10:38.180 --> 00:10:39.456
I think he's in one of those

145
00:10:39.480 --> 00:10:41.746
personal improvement
cults or something.

146
00:10:41.770 --> 00:10:44.150
Well. send my love if
you see him again.

147
00:10:44.770 --> 00:10:46.740
Happy Birthday. Goodnight.

148
00:10:56.500 --> 00:10:57.450
Aw.

149
00:11:15.970 --> 00:11:18.616
From companies that defaulted
on their payments.

150
00:11:18.640 --> 00:11:23.246
The FCC expects to receive
more than $500 million in bids

151
00:11:23.270 --> 00:11:25.860
as the licenses eagerly soar...

152
00:11:26.150 --> 00:11:27.820
Elizabeth. good evening.

153
00:11:28.030 --> 00:11:29.336
Happy Birthday. Nickie.

154
00:11:29.360 --> 00:11:30.820
1140.

155
00:11:30.950 --> 00:11:32.610
You almost missed it this year.

156
00:11:33.490 --> 00:11:35.136
Have you had a nice birthday?

157
00:11:35.160 --> 00:11:37.540
Does Rose Kennedy
have a black dress?

158
00:11:37.910 --> 00:11:41.370
I went. not once. but twice
through the spanking machine.

159
00:11:42.040 --> 00:11:43.670
I can only imagine.

160
00:11:44.460 --> 00:11:45.880
How are you?

161
00:11:46.170 --> 00:11:47.736
Connie asked me the
same thing today.

162
00:11:47.760 --> 00:11:48.840
Connie? Really?

163
00:11:49.220 --> 00:11:50.880
I've always liked your brother.

164
00:11:52.220 --> 00:11:53.760
Anyway...

165
00:11:53.890 --> 00:11:55.526
I... I just thought

166
00:11:55.550 --> 00:11:57.116
this might be
difficult for you...

167
00:11:57.140 --> 00:11:58.770
Just another birthday.

168
00:11:59.850 --> 00:12:01.810
Because of your father.

169
00:12:02.480 --> 00:12:04.496
That's right.
He was 48. wasn't he?

170
00:12:04.520 --> 00:12:07.020
I hadn't really thought
about it until now.

171
00:12:07.070 --> 00:12:09.610
Why do I call?

172
00:12:11.150 --> 00:12:13.336
I honestly don't know.

173
00:12:13.360 --> 00:12:15.660
Please send Dr.
Mel and Rachel my best.

174
00:12:16.330 --> 00:12:18.200
She has a little
brother on the way.

175
00:12:18.700 --> 00:12:20.410
We did the ultrasound.

176
00:12:20.830 --> 00:12:22.540
Official nuclear family.

177
00:12:23.750 --> 00:12:25.330
You must be very pleased.

178
00:12:25.500 --> 00:12:26.670
We are.

179
00:12:26.840 --> 00:12:28.420
We are very pleased.

180
00:12:28.670 --> 00:12:30.670
Well. it's good
to talk with you.

181
00:12:31.800 --> 00:12:33.510
I guess I should let you go.

182
00:12:33.680 --> 00:12:35.366
Take care of yourself.

183
00:12:35.390 --> 00:12:37.196
You too. Nicholas. I mean that.

184
00:12:37.220 --> 00:12:39.600
I really do. Uh-huh.
Be well. Bye.

185
00:12:40.890 --> 00:12:44.916
A proposal to encourage small
businesses to provide their employees

186
00:12:44.940 --> 00:12:49.230
with health insurance is now being
debated by Washington legislators.

187
00:12:49.440 --> 00:12:52.086
The bill which attaches a
small-business health plan

188
00:12:52.110 --> 00:12:54.136
to those of larger corporations

189
00:12:54.160 --> 00:12:58.370
is receiving initial support from a
number of key Republican leaders.

190
00:12:58.540 --> 00:13:02.266
However. Democratic lawmakers
are voicing serious concerns

191
00:13:02.290 --> 00:13:06.460
about the bill. claiming that it
would undermine local efforts...

192
00:13:31.690 --> 00:13:35.110
I just wanna make sure that
we understand each other.

193
00:13:35.240 --> 00:13:39.370
Once you get it down on paper then
you can count on my full support.

194
00:13:40.330 --> 00:13:42.346
We understand that. Thank you.

195
00:13:42.370 --> 00:13:43.580
We'll talk soon.

196
00:14:20.870 --> 00:14:23.306
Well. you shouldn't feel this
reflects negatively on you.

197
00:14:23.330 --> 00:14:25.726
I do feel that it reflects
negatively on me.

198
00:14:25.750 --> 00:14:27.606
I received this...
Just a moment.

199
00:14:27.630 --> 00:14:29.226
I took these tests
in good faith.

200
00:14:29.250 --> 00:14:30.960
I'm sorry you feel that way.

201
00:14:31.380 --> 00:14:32.856
I understand.

202
00:14:32.880 --> 00:14:35.026
We hope we haven't caused
you any inconvenience.

203
00:14:35.050 --> 00:14:37.180
Thank you for choosing CRS.

204
00:14:37.390 --> 00:14:40.116
Mr. Feingold. could you
assist this gentleman?

205
00:14:40.140 --> 00:14:42.140
Oh. yeah. Sure.

206
00:14:43.140 --> 00:14:45.416
Jim Feingold. VP
Engineering. Data Analysis.

207
00:14:45.440 --> 00:14:47.956
I don't know exactly how this works.
My brother sent me this card...

208
00:14:47.980 --> 00:14:49.900
Oh. here we go. Yeah.
...as a gift.

209
00:14:50.110 --> 00:14:52.530
All right. excellent.
Well. let's get started.

210
00:14:52.650 --> 00:14:56.700
Yeah. I'm sorry about the...
You know. all this hullabaloo here.

211
00:14:56.740 --> 00:14:59.410
We're. uh... Well.
we're still moving.

212
00:14:59.620 --> 00:15:02.330
I got an office around
here somewhere.

213
00:15:04.700 --> 00:15:06.410
You mind holding that?

214
00:15:08.000 --> 00:15:09.460
Thank you very much.

215
00:15:12.300 --> 00:15:13.510
Thank you.

216
00:15:13.630 --> 00:15:15.446
Are you hungry? New Moon Cafe.

217
00:15:15.470 --> 00:15:16.550
No. thank you.

218
00:15:16.720 --> 00:15:18.050
Next to Chinatown.

219
00:15:23.180 --> 00:15:25.680
A gift from Conrad Van Orton.

220
00:15:27.060 --> 00:15:28.746
Interesting. What is?

221
00:15:28.770 --> 00:15:31.730
Well. your brother was a
client with our London branch.

222
00:15:32.110 --> 00:15:34.126
We do a sort of
informal scoring.

223
00:15:34.150 --> 00:15:36.756
and his numbers are outstanding.

224
00:15:36.780 --> 00:15:38.160
Really? Hmm.

225
00:15:38.490 --> 00:15:40.046
You sure you're not hungry?
No. thank you.

226
00:15:40.070 --> 00:15:43.926
Okay. fine. Now. you need
to fill out these forms.

227
00:15:43.950 --> 00:15:45.846
There's an application

228
00:15:45.870 --> 00:15:48.726
and then a couple of psych-tests there.
A MNPI and a PAP.

229
00:15:48.750 --> 00:15:50.936
Oh. uh. for the financial
questionnaire.

230
00:15:50.960 --> 00:15:52.750
don't answer anything
you don't feel like.

231
00:15:53.340 --> 00:15:55.010
We'll run our TRW.

232
00:15:55.550 --> 00:15:58.680
"I sometimes hurt small
animals. true or false"?

233
00:16:01.390 --> 00:16:03.680
"I feel guilty when
I masturbate."

234
00:16:04.180 --> 00:16:06.350
Well. I don't write
the questions.

235
00:16:07.100 --> 00:16:09.560
I just review the answers.

236
00:16:13.770 --> 00:16:14.940
What is this for?

237
00:16:15.480 --> 00:16:17.546
Well. to give us an overall
sense of your capability...

238
00:16:17.570 --> 00:16:20.490
No. what is this for?
What are you selling?

239
00:16:21.780 --> 00:16:22.830
Oh.

240
00:16:23.240 --> 00:16:25.306
It's a game. A game?

241
00:16:25.330 --> 00:16:28.120
Specifically tailored
for each participant.

242
00:16:28.750 --> 00:16:31.750
Think of it as a great vacation.
Except you don't go to it.

243
00:16:32.250 --> 00:16:33.476
it comes to you.

244
00:16:33.500 --> 00:16:35.630
What... What kind of vacation?

245
00:16:36.590 --> 00:16:38.066
It's different every time.

246
00:16:38.090 --> 00:16:39.800
Humor me with specifics.

247
00:16:40.130 --> 00:16:41.640
We provide

248
00:16:44.850 --> 00:16:46.390
whatever's lacking.

249
00:16:46.600 --> 00:16:48.286
And what if nothing is lacking?

250
00:16:48.310 --> 00:16:49.786
May I make two suggestions?

251
00:16:49.810 --> 00:16:52.876
You really think that I'll
participate without knowing any...

252
00:16:52.900 --> 00:16:56.570
First. admit to yourself
that it sounds intriguing.

253
00:16:57.400 --> 00:16:59.466
Second. you don't
have to decide today.

254
00:16:59.490 --> 00:17:01.676
Take the silly test. fill
out the stupid forms.

255
00:17:01.700 --> 00:17:06.160
One day. your game begins. You either
love it or hate it. Decide then.

256
00:17:06.910 --> 00:17:08.870
You know we... We are like

257
00:17:09.660 --> 00:17:13.000
an experiential
book-of-the-month club.

258
00:17:13.420 --> 00:17:16.340
You can drop out at any time
with no further obligation.

259
00:17:18.670 --> 00:17:20.130
That was my sales pitch.

260
00:17:21.180 --> 00:17:22.640
How long will this take?

261
00:17:22.890 --> 00:17:25.260
About an hour for those.
another hour for the physical.

262
00:17:25.510 --> 00:17:27.696
Physical? It's a
cursory examination.

263
00:17:27.720 --> 00:17:31.520
turn-your-head. cough sort of thing.
You'll be out of here in no time.

264
00:18:20.240 --> 00:18:21.530
Confused.

265
00:18:27.580 --> 00:18:28.580
Risky.

266
00:18:32.620 --> 00:18:33.750
Bloody.

267
00:18:38.500 --> 00:18:39.670
Whoops.

268
00:18:59.860 --> 00:19:01.966
Mr. Sutherland called about
Baer-Grant Publishing.

269
00:19:01.990 --> 00:19:03.836
Cancel it. Push it
back till Wednesday.

270
00:19:03.860 --> 00:19:06.596
And Anson Baer called about tomorrow.
Tomorrow?

271
00:19:06.620 --> 00:19:08.950
Yes. that's correct. How much
longer is this going to take?

272
00:19:09.120 --> 00:19:11.136
Shouldn't be long.
We're almost done.

273
00:19:11.160 --> 00:19:13.056
You said that two hours ago.

274
00:19:13.080 --> 00:19:14.596
All right. Put it
back until tomorrow.

275
00:19:14.620 --> 00:19:16.960
Selection before the following
emotional responses.

276
00:19:17.000 --> 00:19:20.090
You have 0.9 seconds to enter
your emotional response.

277
00:19:20.840 --> 00:19:22.840
Reaction time is a factor.

278
00:19:25.590 --> 00:19:28.810
Please make a selection for the
following emotional responses.

279
00:19:28.930 --> 00:19:31.640
You have 0.9 seconds to enter
your emotional response.

280
00:19:35.400 --> 00:19:36.810
Does this thing end?

281
00:19:52.700 --> 00:19:54.186
I'm sorry to keep you waiting.

282
00:19:54.210 --> 00:19:57.556
Oh. don't worry. It's been just
terrific spending my entire day

283
00:19:57.580 --> 00:19:58.646
with your crack team.

284
00:19:58.670 --> 00:20:00.316
Well. it's all down to this.

285
00:20:00.340 --> 00:20:03.026
This is an insurance company requirement.
It states that you're aware

286
00:20:03.050 --> 00:20:06.276
that the game exists. that you're a
willing participant in said game.

287
00:20:06.300 --> 00:20:08.526
so on and so forth.
Our guarantee. payment's entirely

288
00:20:08.550 --> 00:20:12.286
at your brother's discretion as a gift.
It's dependent on your satisfaction.

289
00:20:12.310 --> 00:20:14.666
Does that mean that if I'm not
happy he doesn't have to pay?

290
00:20:14.690 --> 00:20:17.286
That's never happened. We've never
had an unsatisfied customer.

291
00:20:17.310 --> 00:20:19.190
I think you mean. dissatisfied.

292
00:20:19.520 --> 00:20:21.506
That's right. You're a
left-brained word fetishist.

293
00:20:21.530 --> 00:20:24.296
Initials. initials.
and sign there

294
00:20:24.320 --> 00:20:25.466
in blood.

295
00:20:25.490 --> 00:20:26.660
Just kidding.

296
00:20:28.870 --> 00:20:32.040
All right. Now. your copy will be
at the front desk in this folder.

297
00:20:32.200 --> 00:20:34.016
And I'll... Keep the pen.

298
00:20:34.040 --> 00:20:35.620
We'll let you know.

299
00:20:39.210 --> 00:20:40.396
What about Monday or Tuesday?

300
00:20:40.420 --> 00:20:41.816
No. that's bad for me.

301
00:20:41.840 --> 00:20:42.896
Well. how about tonight?

302
00:20:42.920 --> 00:20:45.300
Well. I'm working
all this evening.

303
00:20:46.090 --> 00:20:48.906
Wednesday is the only
possibility right now.

304
00:20:48.930 --> 00:20:50.196
Do you wanna do dinner?

305
00:20:50.220 --> 00:20:51.736
Okay.

306
00:20:51.760 --> 00:20:54.866
By the way. I went to CRS.

307
00:20:54.890 --> 00:20:57.060
Really? What did you think?

308
00:20:57.230 --> 00:21:00.110
Well they seemed just a
little bit disorganized.

309
00:21:00.310 --> 00:21:03.206
Well. when I did it in London
they'd been around a while.

310
00:21:03.230 --> 00:21:04.716
Are you gonna do this?

311
00:21:04.740 --> 00:21:06.780
No. I haven't decided yet.

312
00:21:09.570 --> 00:21:13.516
Telling you. it's like getting in on the
ground floor of the next Disneyland.

313
00:21:13.540 --> 00:21:16.830
CRS won't go public.
They're family-owned.

314
00:21:17.540 --> 00:21:19.106
Stranger things have happened.

315
00:21:19.130 --> 00:21:21.090
No. they haven't. actually.

316
00:21:22.130 --> 00:21:23.486
They opened here.

317
00:21:23.510 --> 00:21:25.510
The game in San Francisco?

318
00:21:25.800 --> 00:21:28.300
See? They're doing fine
without any of us.

319
00:21:33.810 --> 00:21:35.036
Nicholas. How are you?

320
00:21:35.060 --> 00:21:36.576
James. good evening.
Good evening. sir.

321
00:21:36.600 --> 00:21:38.270
We have new members here?

322
00:21:38.600 --> 00:21:40.110
Believe so. sir.

323
00:21:40.730 --> 00:21:41.956
Put their next round on me.

324
00:21:41.980 --> 00:21:43.110
Got you. sir.

325
00:21:46.360 --> 00:21:47.820
No. no. no. no.

326
00:21:48.110 --> 00:21:51.740
Last time I played Pebble I swore I'd
never pick up another club again.

327
00:21:53.290 --> 00:21:55.080
Speaking about games...

328
00:21:55.330 --> 00:21:58.460
Couldn't help but overhear
you talking about CRS.

329
00:22:00.880 --> 00:22:05.316
Well. the reason I mention it is I took the
test today at the Montgomery Street office.

330
00:22:05.340 --> 00:22:07.220
You did? Kudos.

331
00:22:07.340 --> 00:22:09.446
So. yours hasn't started yet?

332
00:22:09.470 --> 00:22:13.140
No. not yet. That was one of
the questions I had for you.

333
00:22:13.970 --> 00:22:16.076
What is it? Oh. what is it?

334
00:22:16.100 --> 00:22:17.560
The eternal question.

335
00:22:18.060 --> 00:22:19.786
You know. I envy you.

336
00:22:19.810 --> 00:22:24.730
I wish I could go back and do it
for the first time all over again.

337
00:22:26.690 --> 00:22:29.950
Here's to new experiences.

338
00:22:33.740 --> 00:22:35.660
Hmm. if you'll excuse
me. I got to go.

339
00:22:35.830 --> 00:22:37.346
Good night. Ted.

340
00:22:37.370 --> 00:22:39.250
Nicholas. Nice to meet you.

341
00:22:42.880 --> 00:22:44.630
So. you played recently?

342
00:22:44.800 --> 00:22:46.670
Oh. about a year ago.

343
00:22:47.050 --> 00:22:50.010
I was working in Los Angeles.

344
00:22:50.180 --> 00:22:52.906
Oh. I hear the London
office is very good. too...

345
00:22:52.930 --> 00:22:56.390
It sounds like a lot of fantasy.
role-playing nonsense. though.

346
00:22:58.600 --> 00:23:00.520
You wanna know what it is?

347
00:23:01.060 --> 00:23:02.860
What it's all about?

348
00:23:03.440 --> 00:23:06.876
John chapter 0 verse 25.

349
00:23:06.900 --> 00:23:08.190
I. um.

350
00:23:08.530 --> 00:23:10.546
haven't been to Sunday
school in a long time.

351
00:23:10.570 --> 00:23:12.030
"Whereas once I was blind."

352
00:23:12.990 --> 00:23:14.450
"now I can see."

353
00:23:16.740 --> 00:23:18.330
Good night. Nicholas.

354
00:23:19.040 --> 00:23:20.330
Best of luck.

355
00:23:20.750 --> 00:23:22.040
Goodnight.

356
00:23:36.390 --> 00:23:38.680
If the Baer-Grant meeting

357
00:23:40.270 --> 00:23:42.730
is not held tomorrow

358
00:23:43.400 --> 00:23:46.400
may as well not be held at all.

359
00:23:48.030 --> 00:23:51.216
When Mr. Van Orton boards
his plane on the morrow

360
00:23:51.240 --> 00:23:55.216
he will have every agreement and
addendum in the complete closing package

361
00:23:55.240 --> 00:23:56.846
flawlessly revised.

362
00:23:56.870 --> 00:24:00.120
So you will miss another opera you
would have slept during anyway.

363
00:24:00.370 --> 00:24:02.896
We now have an opportunity
to show our clients

364
00:24:02.920 --> 00:24:06.170
how well we will rise to his
exhilarating challenge.

365
00:24:08.300 --> 00:24:10.446
Yes. Nicholas Van Orton?

366
00:24:10.470 --> 00:24:13.066
Who is this? This is
Cynthia from CRS.

367
00:24:13.090 --> 00:24:14.316
How did you get this number?

368
00:24:14.340 --> 00:24:16.406
We've finished processing
your application.

369
00:24:16.430 --> 00:24:17.786
Look. I'm in a
meeting right now.

370
00:24:17.810 --> 00:24:19.640
I'm afraid it was rejected.

371
00:24:20.810 --> 00:24:23.496
I beg your pardon? You shouldn't feel
this reflects negatively on you.

372
00:24:23.520 --> 00:24:25.286
We hope we haven't caused
you any inconvenience.

373
00:24:25.310 --> 00:24:28.190
Oh. this is ridiculous.
Thank you for thinking of CRS.

374
00:24:29.610 --> 00:24:31.030
Anything wrong?

375
00:24:31.240 --> 00:24:32.990
Uh. no. No. nothing's...

376
00:24:35.570 --> 00:24:38.966
You may hang up or press
pound for more options.

377
00:24:38.990 --> 00:24:41.540
Oh. this is Conrad.
Leave a message.

378
00:24:42.790 --> 00:24:45.960
Yes. Connie. it's Nicholas.
Give me a ring when you get in.

379
00:24:46.710 --> 00:24:50.066
Oh. uh. regarding your
birthday present.

380
00:24:50.090 --> 00:24:52.606
um. things are a little
crazy right now.

381
00:24:52.630 --> 00:24:54.316
I don't really know if I
can fit it in my schedule.

382
00:24:54.340 --> 00:24:56.656
But we'll talk about
it at dinner tomorrow.

383
00:24:56.680 --> 00:24:58.100
Thanks. bye.

384
00:25:30.920 --> 00:25:32.130
Hello.

385
00:26:33.240 --> 00:26:36.136
The resulting rise of
unemployment and decline

386
00:26:36.160 --> 00:26:38.386
into buyable small businesses.

387
00:26:38.410 --> 00:26:41.216
Meanwhile. Republican leaders
argue that this passage

388
00:26:41.240 --> 00:26:44.710
would be the very stimulant
that a sluggish economy needs.

389
00:26:45.080 --> 00:26:48.056
No one has expressed an opinion
as to how it will impact

390
00:26:48.080 --> 00:26:50.840
the pampered existence
of Nicholas Van Orton.

391
00:26:51.380 --> 00:26:54.566
The one thing on which both Democrats
and Republicans seem to agree

392
00:26:54.590 --> 00:26:58.840
is that most Americans harbor serious
doubts about the economic future.

393
00:26:59.090 --> 00:27:03.946
A recent poll suggests a staggering
57% of American workers believe

394
00:27:03.970 --> 00:27:09.060
