unemployed within the next 5 to 7 years.

395
00:27:09.440 --> 00:27:13.900
But what does that matter to a bloated
millionaire fat cat like you?

396
00:27:14.940 --> 00:27:19.046
In other financial news. stock markets
rose both domestically and abroad today

397
00:27:19.070 --> 00:27:21.756
after the announcement of
stronger than expected earnings

398
00:27:21.780 --> 00:27:23.926
by several high tech companies

399
00:27:23.950 --> 00:27:28.580
but dipped again reacting to reports
that Nicholas Van Orton had sneezed.

400
00:27:31.460 --> 00:27:35.210
Are you gonna spend the rest of the
evening prying at that clown's mouth?

401
00:27:37.130 --> 00:27:41.010
I... I don't... It's frustrating
for me if you don't pay attention.

402
00:27:42.810 --> 00:27:44.270
What is this?

403
00:27:45.020 --> 00:27:48.480
This is your game. Nicholas.
and welcome to it.

404
00:27:49.560 --> 00:27:52.770
I'm here to let you in
on a few ground rules.

405
00:27:53.190 --> 00:27:56.240
You received the very first
key. and others will follow.

406
00:27:56.570 --> 00:28:00.296
You'll never know where you'll find
them or how you'll need to use them.

407
00:28:00.320 --> 00:28:02.240
So keep your eyes open.

408
00:28:02.580 --> 00:28:04.636
How do you... You can see me?

409
00:28:04.660 --> 00:28:07.120
Let us save the questions
till afterwards.

410
00:28:09.330 --> 00:28:10.830
How does this work?

411
00:28:12.750 --> 00:28:16.130
There's a tiny camera
looking at you right now.

412
00:28:17.840 --> 00:28:20.340
It's impossible.
You're right. impossible.

413
00:28:21.300 --> 00:28:24.180
You're having a conversation
with your television.

414
00:28:27.140 --> 00:28:28.640
It's miniaturized.

415
00:28:31.650 --> 00:28:33.860
You know how dangerous that is?

416
00:28:38.950 --> 00:28:41.086
Mr. Van Orton?
And in domestic news.

417
00:28:41.110 --> 00:28:43.200
in Southern California...
Yes. Ilsa. What is it?

418
00:28:43.660 --> 00:28:45.266
Is everything all right?

419
00:28:45.290 --> 00:28:46.556
It's fine. It's...

420
00:28:46.580 --> 00:28:49.186
in the petroleum processing
plant yesterday.

421
00:28:49.210 --> 00:28:52.146
I've finished for the evening.
Will you be needing anything else?

422
00:28:52.170 --> 00:28:54.750
No. I won't. Ilsa. Thank you.
Good night.

423
00:28:55.300 --> 00:28:56.896
Good night. then.

424
00:28:56.920 --> 00:28:59.510
In a petroleum processing
plant yesterday.

425
00:28:59.930 --> 00:29:02.776
Several workers were injured in the...
Who was that?

426
00:29:02.800 --> 00:29:04.390
Never mind who that is.

427
00:29:04.760 --> 00:29:06.946
You wanna know how a camera got
into your home. don't you?

428
00:29:06.970 --> 00:29:08.390
Yes. I would.

429
00:29:16.230 --> 00:29:17.190
Cold.

430
00:29:19.240 --> 00:29:20.530
Colder.

431
00:29:24.870 --> 00:29:26.370
Warm.

432
00:29:30.710 --> 00:29:31.870
Warmer.

433
00:29:47.810 --> 00:29:49.746
Write this number down.

434
00:29:49.770 --> 00:29:53.286
It's a 24-hour Consumer
Recreation Services hotline.

435
00:29:53.310 --> 00:29:54.770
For emergencies only.

436
00:29:54.940 --> 00:29:57.756
But don't call asking what
the object of the game is.

437
00:29:57.780 --> 00:30:00.650
Figuring that out is the
object of the game.

438
00:30:01.450 --> 00:30:05.530
Good luck and congratulations
on choosing CRS.

439
00:30:06.030 --> 00:30:09.676
Regret to have the American ambassador
expelled after the incident.

440
00:30:09.700 --> 00:30:13.476
US State Department responded
quickly with a formal apology.

441
00:30:13.500 --> 00:30:17.300
An announcement of the ambassador's
immediate voluntary removal...

442
00:30:35.110 --> 00:30:37.126
Hey. buddy. spare any change?

443
00:30:37.150 --> 00:30:38.820
Help me out here. huh? Huh?

444
00:30:54.250 --> 00:30:57.290
If you'd like to make a call.
please hang up and try again.

445
00:32:14.290 --> 00:32:15.710
May I help you?

446
00:32:20.090 --> 00:32:21.340
What is it?

447
00:32:25.510 --> 00:32:26.510
What?

448
00:32:35.770 --> 00:32:36.940
Thank you.

449
00:32:49.620 --> 00:32:51.120
Buddy?

450
00:32:54.120 --> 00:32:55.960
Can you help me out?

451
00:32:57.830 --> 00:33:00.000
I need some toilet paper.
I ran out.

452
00:33:02.630 --> 00:33:04.880
Just... Just go into
the next stall.

453
00:33:07.380 --> 00:33:08.970
Come on. help me out.

454
00:33:10.390 --> 00:33:11.430
Hello?

455
00:33:13.270 --> 00:33:14.310
Hello?

456
00:33:19.520 --> 00:33:20.940
Didn't expect to see you here.

457
00:33:21.230 --> 00:33:22.610
I wanted to wish you luck.

458
00:33:23.030 --> 00:33:24.360
Been up all night?

459
00:33:24.530 --> 00:33:26.320
I checked it. Personally.

460
00:33:26.530 --> 00:33:28.836
I appreciate that. Sam. Why don't
you go home and get some sleep?

461
00:33:28.860 --> 00:33:31.556
You're sure you don't want me along?
No. I'll be fine.

462
00:33:31.580 --> 00:33:33.490
Hmm. nice shirt.

463
00:33:34.200 --> 00:33:35.370
Don't ask.

464
00:33:35.700 --> 00:33:36.830
Ciao!

465
00:34:01.560 --> 00:34:03.916
All of these years.

466
00:34:03.940 --> 00:34:06.990
the first time ever you've
stepped foot in these offices.

467
00:34:07.200 --> 00:34:09.240
it's to ask me to step down.

468
00:34:09.410 --> 00:34:11.596
You promised to meet the
projections. Anson.

469
00:34:11.620 --> 00:34:13.910
$1.60 a share is what you said.

470
00:34:14.370 --> 00:34:17.370
I don't think this visit
comes as a surprise.

471
00:34:17.710 --> 00:34:19.306
Projections were far
too optimistic.

472
00:34:19.330 --> 00:34:20.556
Admittedly. yes.

473
00:34:20.580 --> 00:34:23.316
Our EPS was 150 last quarter.
We're up 6 cents...

474
00:34:23.340 --> 00:34:27.380
The expectations were 10. and in this
case the expectations meant everything.

475
00:34:28.090 --> 00:34:30.640
Will you really hold
me to it over pennies?

476
00:34:30.930 --> 00:34:33.076
My stock is falling.
I don't know about yours.

477
00:34:33.100 --> 00:34:36.076
Those pennies are costing millions.
Give me...

478
00:34:36.100 --> 00:34:37.890
Give me next quarter.

479
00:34:38.060 --> 00:34:39.956
If you still feel this
way. vote your shares...

480
00:34:39.980 --> 00:34:41.730
Today is what counts. Anson.

481
00:34:45.190 --> 00:34:46.190
You...

482
00:34:46.900 --> 00:34:49.200
You intractable son of a bitch.

483
00:34:49.610 --> 00:34:51.570
If your father
could see you now.

484
00:34:52.160 --> 00:34:53.870
What? Your father was a friend.

485
00:34:54.660 --> 00:34:56.886
A friend! God damn it.
I've watched you grow up.

486
00:34:56.910 --> 00:35:00.936
Because you went fishing with my
father I should sit on my hands

487
00:35:00.960 --> 00:35:02.686
while you're throwing
my money away?

488
00:35:02.710 --> 00:35:04.476
I will tell you...
I'm not finished.

489
00:35:04.500 --> 00:35:07.670
Now. you misspoke before when
you said you're stepping down.

490
00:35:09.090 --> 00:35:10.930
I am firing you.

491
00:35:11.640 --> 00:35:14.680
Action is taken.
Confidence is restored.

492
00:35:15.600 --> 00:35:17.220
The stock goes up. No.

493
00:35:17.520 --> 00:35:20.916
There's no Baer-Grant
Publishing...

494
00:35:20.940 --> 00:35:25.320
No Baer-Grant Publishing
without Anson Baer.

495
00:35:26.070 --> 00:35:28.836
Where's Stewart Grant?
He's probably out there sailing

496
00:35:28.860 --> 00:35:32.110
enjoying his golden years wondering
where the hell you are. Anson.

497
00:35:33.320 --> 00:35:34.620
I'm sorry.

498
00:35:35.580 --> 00:35:36.950
You failed.

499
00:35:41.080 --> 00:35:45.396
I have prepared a severance
package that is more than

500
00:35:45.420 --> 00:35:46.670
equitable.

501
00:35:47.630 --> 00:35:50.260
Valid until this evening.

502
00:35:52.550 --> 00:35:54.390
I could fight you on this.

503
00:35:55.140 --> 00:35:57.470
If I leave without
your signature.

504
00:35:57.890 --> 00:36:00.640
this agreement begins
to disintegrate.

505
00:36:00.850 --> 00:36:03.576
Benefits shrink. options narrow

506
00:36:03.600 --> 00:36:07.020
and your compensation
will be shriveled.

507
00:36:12.820 --> 00:36:14.530
I think it's in your

508
00:36:14.660 --> 00:36:16.580
best interest. Anson. to...

509
00:36:32.720 --> 00:36:34.510
Well. I guess this is your

510
00:36:35.100 --> 00:36:36.890
lucky day.

511
00:36:38.140 --> 00:36:40.230
My lawyers will be
in touch with you.

512
00:37:13.430 --> 00:37:16.526
Excuse me. Has Conrad Van
Orton left a message?

513
00:37:16.550 --> 00:37:18.196
I'll check on it right away. Mr.
Van Orton.

514
00:37:18.220 --> 00:37:19.470
Thank you.

515
00:37:25.940 --> 00:37:28.456
Oh. I'm so sorry. Here.

516
00:37:28.480 --> 00:37:30.456
Please. don't do that.

